  <li id="comment-1148" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/01/odysseus-and-the-macaroons/#comment-1148"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2007-09-12T15:51:00-04:00">Wednesday, September 12, 2007 at 3:51 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hmm.  You&#8217;ve stumped me, Jana!  I&#8217;ve never considered using cream cheese here, so I have no idea what to tell you!  I can say, though, that I don&#8217;t think you should substitute the egg whites.  I think you need them for the proper texture here.  You might try just adding some cream cheese to the recipe as is &#8211; or, at most, substitute cream cheese for only 1 or 2 egg whites.  </></>Good luck!  Let me know how it turns out&#8230;</p>
    </div>

