  <li id="comment-1168" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/01493708300940204826" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Molly</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2005/01/odysseus-and-the-macaroons/#comment-1168"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-06-10T01:55:17-04:00">Wednesday, June 10, 2009 at 1:55 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Cara, I&#39;m sorry to have not replied sooner!  I&#39;m not sure whether you&#39;ll see this or not, but if so, I do think you&#39;re right: you didn&#39;t cook the coconut mixture long enough.  It should no longer be creamy or wet or at all liquidy.  Individual pieces of coconut should be readily discernible.  You&#39;re looking for a sort of paste of coconut shreds.  I hope that makes sense!</p>
    </div>

